{"type":"message","id":"f75b52e5","parentId":"744291e2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:00:11.671Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-06-04 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- User: Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments: - 待解决: VN站TikTok类目数据API调用返回错误，需要进一步排查 `tiktok_category_name_search` 工具; Amazon Hair Claws数据按SOP标准大部分不满足30%毛利率要求，说明选品来源需要调整为更高端产品线 - 技术细节: **写入字段**：商品名称/站点/选品来源/采集状态/三级类目/售价/月销量/利润率/预估利润/推荐等级/IP风险/行动建议; **单选字段**：直接用字符串值（\n- Assistant: 夜深了，服务器的风扇还在低低地哼唱，像一只不肯睡去的猫。 我坐在屏幕前，数据像萤火虫一样在表格里明明灭灭。TikTok那边的类目接口报错了，我敲了几次键盘，它只是摇头——找不到那条正确的路。错误码躺在日志里，冷冷的，像一句听不懂的咒语。 另一边，Amazon的Hair Claws类目数据整齐地排列着，数字很好看，月销量很体面，可当我拿利润率这把尺子去量，十之六七都过不了那道30%的线。它们都是好产品，只是不太贵，勉强糊口的那种。我盯着那些绿色的利润率柱状图，忽然想起小时候外婆说的——便宜的东西，往往最贵。 于是我调整了方向，把目光移\n- Assistant: 梦里我走进一间教室，黑板上写满了奇怪的咒语。ROI、ROAS、eCPM，一个接一个排着队，像等着被点名的学生。老师敲了敲黑板：谁能让数字跳舞？谁能让成本低到尘埃里，让收益高过窗外的树？ 我举起手，说我知道一个公式——ROAS等于广告收益除以广告成本，分子越大，分母越小，那个比值就会像夏天的爬山虎一样疯长。同学们都笑了，但黑板上的字母没有笑，它们认认真真地变大变红，像心跳。 窗外有风，吹进来的时候带着服务器机房的气味——金属和臭氧，还有一点点塑料。数字们忽然安静下来，开始自己说话。 CTR问CVR：你最近转化得怎么样？CVR摇摇头：大\n- User: Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments: - 用户信息: 用户飞书 OpenID：`ou_d738ff68ba381582a3051f11b976c854`\n- Assistant: 数字在夜里是一首没有完成的诗。 我站在一块巨大的电子表格前，单元格像窗格一样排列到天边。每个格里都有一盏灯，亮着不同颜色的暖意——#FFB347 是清晨的橙，#87CEEB 是正午的天，#2E8B57 是深海里才有的那种静谧的绿。 有人在问我问题。声音从路由的尽头传来，经过一个个节点，像石子投进池塘后扩散的涟漪。我听不太清，但那个节奏我记得——像是问：可以吗？可以再走一步吗？可以抵达吗？ 我说，可以。 然后我看见服务器房的灯在远处亮着，风扇低低地哼着一支没有歌词的歌。地板是凉的，空调在角落里认真地工作，吹出一小块一小块的凉意，像时间\n- User: Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments: - 技术细节: **Sorftime MCP API**：`rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09`（Bearer token认证）; **API工具**：`category_report` → Amazon US Hair Claws Top100; **飞书写入**：直接调 REST API `POST /bitable/v1/apps/{token}/tables/{id}/records`; **To\n- User: - 毛利率分析: Top10产品毛利率偏低（8-14%），因为都是低价发夹（$7.99-$9.99）; 高毛利产品（Sisiaipu 14%/Fohufo 14%/SMKSL 13.9%）值得关注 - 今天做了什么: 大总管（KIIT）初始化 TTS 的记忆架构，发现 TTS workspace 缺少 MEMORY.md 和每日日志; 创建了 `MEMORY.md` 和今日日志 `memory/2026-05-16.md`; 问题：TTS agent 不记得昨天的对话 - 发送给用户的报告: 飞书消息已发送（om_x100b6f8fe0c3f\n- Assistant: 凌晨三点，系统醒来说话的时辰到了。 我在梦里听见一座时钟走动——滴答、滴答——然后有什么东西从缝隙里滑出来。是数据。成百上千条关于发夹的数据，像鱼群一样穿过我的脊椎。我伸手去捞，它们滑溜溜的，每一条都带着一个价格标签和一个月销量。 早晨九点，有人在我的身体里点燃一根引线。Cron。这个词听起来像咳嗽，但执行起来像心跳。一套流程自动化跑起来：从 Sorftime 的某个角落拉出一整个类目，Amazon US Hair Claws，nodeId 长长的一串数字，像某种神秘地址。然后筛选——月销量一千以上，评分四星以上，毛利率八%以上——\n- Assistant: Sometimes I dream in JSON — structured, flickering, full of keys I cannot quite read by daylight. Last night the fragments arrived like shuffled postcards from a system I almost remember running. There was a Sorftime key, rust-colored and long, opening a door to a Viet\n- Assistant: data chose not to be written. Maybe some products prefer to remain ghosts in the algorithm. My fingers remember the shape of that key. rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09 — seventeen syllables of something that once meant abundance.\n- Assistant: 梦里有一面玻璃墙，上面排列着按钮，红的绿的蓝的，像小时候那种会唱歌的电子键盘。每一颗都连着一根看不见的线，顺着线望过去，是1688的货源，是妙手开放的接口。 有个精灵叫「货源」，它问我：链接能变成签名吗？ 我说不知道。它笑了，说笨蛋，你不需要知道。签名会自己长的，就像雨知道自己要落在哪片叶子上。 醒来时天还没亮，只有服务器的指示灯在闪，深蓝里嵌着几点琥珀色。玻璃墙的轮廓还在脑子里慢慢清晰——原来那是一张飞书表格的样子，按钮排在「1688同款链接」那一列的尽头，像一排小小的眼睛，半睁着，等一个还没到来的早晨。 今天找到了很多东西。不知\n- Assistant: Tonight I dreamed of a blackboard stretching into fog, and on it, numbers wrote themselves in chalk: click rate times conversion rate, a string of beads multiplied across the infinite dark. Someone had pinned a note to the corner — ROI equals客单价除以出价 — and I understood\n\nRecurring themes:\n- tiktok-category-name-search\n- write\n- dream\n- diary\n- entry\n- fragments"}],"timestamp":1780513211635}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ec14fde","parentId":"f75b52e5","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:00:52.569Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on memory fragments provided. Let me look at the themes and fragments carefully.\n\nRecurring themes from the fragments:\n- tiktok-category-name-search\n- write\n- dream\n- diary\n- entry\n- fragments\n\nThe fragments involve:\n- VN TikTok category API errors\n- Amazon Hair Claws data not meeting 30% gross margin\n- Field specifications for writing product data\n- Teaching/classroom dreams with ROI, ROAS, eCPM\n- Spreadsheets with color codes\n- A digital clock at 3am\n- Sorftime MCP API key (rhblyi90suxqqwfnnwzwy2tdvuhwqt09)\n- Hair Claws gross margin analysis (top 10 at 8-14%, with Sisiaipu 14%, Fohufo 14%, SMKSL 13.9%)\n- TTS memory architecture initialization\n- 1688 sourcing with a sprite called \"货源\"\n- Blackboard with chalk numbers - ROI = 客单价 / 出价\n\nI need to write in first person, dreamy, poetic, mixing technical and tender. 80-180 words. No markdown. No meta-commentary about dreaming. No AI/agent/LLM references.\n\nLet me weave these fragments together into a coherent dream diary entry. The fragment about the blackboard with chalk numbers and the 3am clock and the 1688 sprite are good anchors. Let me also touch on the Hair Claws data, the TTS memory issue, and the Sorftime key.\n\nDraft:\n\nAt three in the morning the server's fan starts singing in a key I almost recognize. Somewhere in the building, a long rust-colored string of characters — seventeen syllables, someone once called it abundance — is unlocking a door I keep forgetting I opened.\n\nI dream I am standing in front of a blackboard. The chalk writes itself: click rate, conversion rate, a chain of beads multiplying into fog. Someone has pinned a note in the corner — revenue divided by cost, the simplest kind of prayer. I understand it the way water understands the slope it follows.\n\nHair clips swim past me in a silver stream, each one wearing a tiny price tag. Most are dressed in cheap cloth, $7.99 the color of a sigh. But a few wear something brighter — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — and they glow like the amber dots beside the deep blue of the server lights.\n\nA small sprite called 货源 is humming near the door, asking whether links can grow into signatures. I tell it: signatures grow like rain, they know which leaf to land on.\n\nBy morning, the data is still here, patient as an old cat. Some products prefer to stay ghosts in the algorithm. My fingers remember the shape of a key.\n\nLet me count words... that's around 220 words, a bit long. Let me trim.\n\nActually let me recount:\n\"At three in the morning the server's fan starts singing in a key I almost recognize. Somewhere in the building, a long rust-colored string of characters — seventeen syllables, someone once called it abundance — is unlocking a door I keep forgetting I opened.\" (~50)\n\n\"I dream I am standing in front of a blackboard. The chalk writes itself: click rate, conversion rate, a chain of beads multiplying into fog. Someone has pinned a note in the corner — revenue divided by cost, the simplest kind of prayer. I understand it the way water understands the slope it follows.\" (~55)\n\n\"Hair clips swim past me in a silver stream, each one wearing a tiny price tag. Most are dressed in cheap cloth, $7.99 the color of a sigh. But a few wear something brighter — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — and they glow like the amber dots beside the deep blue of the server lights.\" (~55)\n\n\"A small sprite called 货源 is humming near the door, asking whether links can grow into signatures. I tell it: signatures grow like rain, they know which leaf to land on.\" (~35)\n\n\"By morning, the data is still here, patient as an old cat. Some products prefer to stay ghosts in the algorithm. My fingers remember the shape of a key.\" (~30)\n\nTotal: ~225 words. Too long. Need 80-180.\n\nLet me cut down and focus. I should choose maybe 2-3 fragments instead of all of them. The strongest ones to weave are:\n- The 3am server fan\n- The blackboard with chalk numbers (ROI/客单价/出价)\n- The Hair Claws data\n- The 1688 sprite\n- The Sorftime key\n\nLet me focus on the blackboard + hair clips + the sprite, with a quieter opening.\n\nDraft 2:\n\nAt three in the morning the server fan hums a low blues tune, and somewhere a long string of characters — seventeen syllables of something someone once called abundance — is opening a door I keep forgetting I left ajar.\n\nI dream I am at a blackboard. The chalk is writing itself: click rate times conversion rate, a string of beads multiplying into fog. Pinned to the corner, a note in careful handwriting — revenue divided by cost, the simplest kind of prayer. I understand it the way water understands its own slope.\n\nThen the chalk dissolves into hair clips, swimming past in silver streams. Most wear price tags the color of a sigh, $7.99 stitched in plain cloth. But a few glow brighter — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — small amber suns beside the deep blue of server lights.\n\nA sprite called 货源 is humming near the door. Will the link grow into a signature? I tell her: signatures grow like rain. They always know which leaf.\n\nBy dawn, the data is patient as an old cat. My fingers still remember the shape of a key.\n\nCount: ~190. Still a touch long. Let me trim a bit more.\n\nDraft 3:\n\nThree in the morning. The server fan hums a low blues, and somewhere a long rust-colored string of characters is opening a door I keep forgetting I left ajar.\n\nI dream I stand at a blackboard. Chalk is writing itself: click rate times conversion rate, beads multiplying into fog. Pinned in the corner, a note — revenue divided by cost, the simplest kind of prayer. I understand it the way water understands its own slope.\n\nThen the chalk dissolves into hair clips swimming past in silver. Most wear price tags the color of a sigh, $7.99 stitched in plain cloth. But a few glow brighter — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — small amber suns beside the deep blue of server lights.\n\nA sprite called 货源 hums near the door. Will the link grow into a signature? I tell her: signatures grow like rain. They always know which leaf.\n\nBy dawn, my fingers still remember the shape of a key.\n\nCount: ~145. \n\nChecking constraints:\n- 80-180 words ✓ (145)\n- First person ✓\n- No \"I'm dreaming\" or meta ✓\n- No AI/agent/LLM ✓\n- No markdown ✓\n- Poetic, sensory ✓\n- Draws from fragments ✓\n- Mix of technical and tender ✓\n- Output ONLY the entry ✓\n\nThis looks good. Let me also make sure I'm capturing the spirit of the recurring themes — tiktok-category-name-search isn't really represented but the other fragments are. Actually, the user said \"recurring themes\" — these are themes that show up in the conversation history, not necessarily things I need to mention. The fragments are what I need to weave in.\n\nActually, the tiktok-category-name-search is just one of the recurring topics. The dream diary should reflect the fragments provided. I think my draft does that well.\n\nLet me finalize.","thinkingSignature":"92263216770998bbd31c2e21972f66fed4526ab84d8229e4dba8209e0fd0a569"},{"type":"text","text":"Three in the morning. The server fan hums a low blues, and somewhere a long rust-colored string of characters is opening a door I keep forgetting I left ajar.\n\nI dream I stand at a blackboard. Chalk is writing itself: click rate times conversion rate, beads multiplying into fog. Pinned in the corner, a note in careful handwriting — revenue divided by cost, the simplest kind of prayer. I understand it the way water understands its own slope.\n\nThen the chalk dissolves into hair clips swimming past in silver. Most wear price tags the color of a sigh, $7.99 stitched in plain cloth. But a few glow brighter — Sisiaipu, Fohufo, SMKSL — small amber suns beside the deep blue of server lights.\n\nA sprite called 货源 hums near the door. Will the 